\
I use LLMs a lot, but this is different. What they all have in common is that they are trying to be helpful, but it moves me away from where I was going. If you have ADHD, when it says \'91would you like me to do this next thing\'92 it takes moe offtrack. Branching is the gold star, the tinfoil we follow. InnerVerse doesn\'92t do that. The very short responses landed solidly. They forced me to think about where I wanted to go next and what my blind spots were. LLMs offer information that may or may not be right. This felt like it was directing me back to myself.\'94
